1ï¸âƒ£ IF()
Purpose

Checks a condition and returns different results for TRUE and FALSE.

Syntax
=IF(condition, value_if_true, value_if_false)

Example

If A1 = 60 (Marks):

=IF(A1>=50,"Pass","Fail")

Result
Pass

2ï¸âƒ£ AND()
Purpose

Checks multiple conditions.
Returns TRUE only if ALL conditions are TRUE.

Syntax
=AND(condition1, condition2, ...)

Example

If A1 = 75:

=AND(A1>=50, A1<=100)

Result
TRUE

AND with IF (Real Use Case)
=IF(AND(A1>=50, A1<=100),"Pass","Fail")

3ï¸âƒ£ OR()
Purpose

Checks multiple conditions.
Returns TRUE if ANY ONE condition is TRUE.

Syntax
=OR(condition1, condition2, ...)

Example

If A1 = 40:

=OR(A1>=50, A1=40)

Result
TRUE

OR with IF (Real Use Case)
=IF(OR(A1="Saturday", A1="Sunday"),"Holiday","Working Day")

4ï¸âƒ£ IFERROR()
Purpose

Handles Excel errors and replaces them with a clean value.

Syntax
=IFERROR(formula, value_if_error)

Example 1 (Division)

If:

A1 = 10
B1 = 0

